We need bash command to count business days (Mon-Fri) in current month. Use date, seq, etc. Compute first day and last day. Then loop days, count if weekday not Sat Sun. Use GNU date. Command: 

```
first=$(date +%Y-%m-01); last=$(date -d "$(date +%Y-%m-01) +1 month -1 day" +%Y-%m-%d); count=$(seq -f "%Y-%m-%d" -s " " $(date -d "$first" +%s) $(date -d "$last" +%s) 86400 | awk '{
  cmd="date -d \""$0"\" +%u";
  cmd | getline wday;
  close(cmd);
  if (wday<6) c++
} END{print c}');
echo $count
```

But need one line. Combine. Use bash one-liner:

```
first=$(date +%Y-%m-01); last=$(date -d "$first +1 month -1 day" +%Y-%m-%d); seq -f "%Y-%m-%d" -s " " $(date -d "$first" +%s) $(date -d "$last" +%s) 86400 | awk '{cmd="date -d \""$0"\" +%u"; cmd | getline w; close(cmd); if (w<6) c++} END{print c}'
```

That's one line.

